Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the Community Choice Credit Union Convention Center in Des Moines, Iowa. He thanked the Family Leader organization and its leaders, Bob and Darla Vander Plaats, for their work in promoting conservative and pro-family values. Pence discussed the importance of faith in American history and praised the leadership of Dr. Ben Carson. He emphasized the accomplishments of the Trump administration, including rebuilding the military, reviving the economy, and appointing conservative judges. Pence also highlighted the administration's support for law enforcement, its pro-life stance, and its commitment to religious freedom. He criticized Joe Biden and the radical left, warning that they would take the country down a path towards socialism. Pence urged the audience to reelect President Trump for four more years and encouraged them to pray for the nation's challenges. He shared a personal story of his own faith journey and concluded by expressing his belief that the best days for America are yet to come.